# Code owners for security-critical paths.
#
# GitHub auto-requests a review from the listed owner when a pull request changes
# a matching path. This is defense-in-depth alongside the fork gate in
# .github/workflows/external-pr-gate.yml (which hard-blocks all fork PRs).
#
# Enforcement note: a requested code-owner review only *blocks* merging when the
# main branch ruleset has "require code owner review" enabled. That toggle is
# intentionally left OFF so the auto-delegation agent keeps merging its own
# internal PRs without a second approver. Turn it on if you want protocol/auth
# changes to require a human owner's approval as well — be aware that, because
# the agent runs as the repo owner and GitHub forbids approving one's own PR,
# enabling it means agent-authored PRs touching these paths will need a
# different maintainer to approve.

# RADIUS / EAP / RadSec protocol core and vendor handling
/internal/radiusd/        @jamiesun

# Admin API authorization, validation and backup/restore helpers
/internal/adminapi/       @jamiesun

# Persistent data model / schema
/internal/domain/         @jamiesun

# Dependency manifests (supply-chain surface)
/go.mod                   @jamiesun
/go.sum                   @jamiesun

# CI / release / security workflows and the agent skill library
/.github/                 @jamiesun
/.agents/                 @jamiesun
